#Text=Jenny O.
#Text=For the major turkey products company , see Jennie-O .
#Text=Jennifer Anne Ognibene
#Text=, known by her stage name Jenny O. , is an American singer-songwriter , based in Los Angeles , California .
#Text=Early life and education
#Text=Jenny O. grew up on Long Island , New York . [ 1 ]
#Text=She studied Jazz at State University of New York at New Paltz and Composition at State University of New York at Purchase Conservatory of Music . [ 2 ]
#Text=Career
#Text=2010-2012 : Home EP
#Text=In 2010 , Jenny O. released a five-song EP of demo recordings titled Home . [ 3 ]
#Text=The first single , " Well OK Honey , " appeared in the real-guitar-based video game Rocksmith , [ 4 ] HBO ' s True Blood , [ 5 ] and a television campaign by Toyota . [ 6 ]
#Text=In the same year , " Wo n't Let You Leave " was licensed by Subaru in a television campaign . [ 7 ]
#Text=Jenny was a member of the LA Ladies Choir , who released one album , " Sing Joyfully " on Teenage Teardrops Records in 2010 . [ 8 ]
#Text=2013-2015 : Automechanic & Holy Trinity Records
#Text=On February 5 , 2013 , Jenny O. released a full-length album , Automechanic on her own label , Holy Trinity Records . [ 9 ]
#Text=The album was produced by Jonathan Wilson in Echo Park , Los Angeles and features James Gadson on drums . [ 10 ]
#Text=2016 : Work EP
#Text=On October 7 , 2016 , Jenny O. released a second EP of demo recordings , titled Work . [ 11 ]
#Text=The first single , " Cheer Up Free Your Mind , " was re-recorded in Simlish for The Sims 4 video game .
#Text=" Case Study B " plays in Episode 605 of Orange Is The New Black . [ 5 ]
#Text=2017-2019 : Peace & Information
#Text=Peace & Information
#Text=, Jenny O. ’ s second full-length album , was produced by Jonathan Wilson and released August 4 , 2017 on Holy Trinity Records . [ 12 ]
#Text=The song " Trauma Jules " was licensed by the U.S. television series Shameless .
#Text=" Power & Charm " appears in Riverdale . [ 5 ]
#Text=Other Recordings
#Text=" Get Down For The Holidays " , The Christmas Gig , a Target holiday compilation , 2010 .
#Text=" I 'm Gonna Love You Too " by Buddy Holly , Rave On Buddy Holly , Fantasy Records/Concord Music Group , 2011 .
